        title: 'Conclusion',
        text: 'Investing is intimate—part art, part talent, part luck. Like lovemaking, it is too enjoyable for many to abandon. Spotting undervalued stocks and compelling stories feels exhilarating when markets agree.\n\nNo guide fits every case, yet broad guidelines help:\n\n• Allocate assets to needs and risk appetite; consistent saving compounds.\n• Favor companies with growth histories inspiring prudent risk-taking.\n• Trade minimally; align selections with temperament and needs.\n\nThis summary touched taxes, reserves, and lifecycle division.\n\nMaking money need not be mysterious. Resist seductive brief wins. That lesson is simple and essential.\n\nTry this\n\nApply stock-buying principles to your profile. Invest on calculations, not assumptions. Best investors understand enough to ignore fluke profits.\n\nRead it till the end?',
